      • moveForward

        public abstract autopark.CarState moveForward()
        This method moves the car 1 meter forward, queries the two sensors through the isEmpty method described below and returns a data structure that contains the current position of the car, and the situation of the detected parking places up to now. The car cannot be moved forward beyond the end of the street.

        Pre-conditions:
        • position < streetLength
        • moveCar instanceof autopark.Actuator
        • !parked

        Post-condition: None
        Test-cases:
        Returns:
        State of the car

      • isEmpty

        public abstract boolean isEmpty()
        This method queries the two ultrasound sensors at least 5 times and filters the noise in their results and returns the distance to the nearest object in the right hand side. If one sensor is detected to continuously return very noisy output, it is completely disregarded.

        Pre-condition: ultrasound1 instanceof autopark.Sensor
        ultrasound2 instanceof autopark.Sensor
        Post-condition: None
        Test-cases:
        Returns:
        Whether or not the current space observed by the sensors is empty

      • moveBackward

        public abstract autopark.CarState moveBackward()
        The same as above; only it moves the car 1 meter backwards. The car cannot be moved behind if it is already at the beginning of the street.

        Pre-conditions: 0 < position
        moveCar instanceof autopark.Actuator
        Post-condition: None
        Test-cases:
        Returns:
        State of the car

      • park

        public abstract boolean park()
        It moves the car to the beginning of the current 5 meter free stretch of parking place, if it is already detected or moves the car forwards towards the end of the street until such a stretch is detected. Then it performs a pre-programmed reverse parallel parking maneuver.

        Pre-conditions: !parked
        parallelPark instanceof autopark.Actuator
        5 <= parkingSpace
        Post-condition: None
        Test-cases:
        Returns:
        If parking was successful or not

      • unPark

        public abstract boolean unPark()
        It moves the car forward (and to left) to front of the parking place, if it is parked.

        Pre-conditions: parked
        moveCar instanceof autopark.Actuator
        Post-condition: None
        Test-cases:
        Returns:
        If un-parking was successful or not
